<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="396" pageId="2" pageNumber="395" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[2022,2616,2694,3116]" pageId="2" pageNumber="395">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. M. Allen" authorityYear="1923" box="[2025,2198,2886,2919]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="395" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="excelsus">Sorex excelsus</taxonomicName>
has been recognized as valid species relative to S. asperand S. tundrenss. A recent molecular study strongly supported S. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. M. Allen" authorityYear="1923" box="[2106,2202,3004,3037]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="395" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="excelsus">excelsus</taxonomicName>
as a clade well embedded in S. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[2058,2184,3043,3076]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="395" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bedfordiae">bedfordiae</taxonomicName>
, making the later paraphyletic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[2022,2616,2694,3116]" lastBlockId="3.[159,1370,294,1272]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="396" pageId="2" pageNumber="395">
Examination of holotypes of S. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. M. Allen" authorityYear="1923" box="[2461,2557,3083,3116]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="395" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="excelsus">excelsus</taxonomicName>
and S. b. gomphus from Yunnan found that skulls differed, indicating 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. M. Allen" authorityYear="1923" box="[1082,1212,297,322]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="excelsus">S. excelsus</taxonomicName>
was a valid species, and taxonomic revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[658,817,327,360]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bedfordiae">S. bedfordiae</taxonomicName>
was warranted. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
